Program runs successfully. Here's the summary:

---

**Two APIs on `JsonSerializerOptions`:**

| Goal | API | Returns |
|------|-----|---------|
| Get typed metadata (throws if missing) | `options.GetTypeInfo(typeof(T))` → cast to `JsonTypeInfo<T>` | `JsonTypeInfo<T>` |
| Probe without throwing | `options.TryGetTypeInfo(typeof(T), out JsonTypeInfo? info)` | `bool` |

The key file (`Program.cs`):

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;
using System.Text.Json.Serialization;
using System.Text.Json.Serialization.Metadata;

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions { TypeInfoResolver = new DefaultJsonTypeInfoResolver() };

// 1) Strongly-typed retrieval
JsonTypeInfo<Person> personInfo = (JsonTypeInfo<Person>)options.GetTypeInfo(typeof(Person));

// 2) Probe without throwing — returns false instead of throwing
var limited = new JsonSerializerOptions { TypeInfoResolver = JsonTypeInfoResolver.Combine() };
if (limited.TryGetTypeInfo(typeof(Person), out JsonTypeInfo? info))
    Console.WriteLine($"Found: {info!.Type.Name}");
else
    Console.WriteLine("Not available (no exception).");
```

`TryGetTypeInfo` (available since .NET 9) is the no-throw probe you're looking for.
